{
  "texts": [
    "JHEP04(2024)048A natural way to generate the full spectrum of physical states is to begin with the states in the string theory that correspond to the ground states in the dual CFT.",
    "In particular, the w-spectrally flowed sector of the string theory gives rise to the w-twisted sector of the CFT [7].",
    "For odd w, the w-twisted ground states correspond to [|Φ w ⟩] σ w, 22 where|Φ w ⟩ = χ - -w-1 2 ψ - -w-1 2 • • • χ - -1 ψ - -1 χ - 0 ψ - 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩,(3.3)andm 1 + m 2 = - w 2 + 1 4w, m 1 -m 2 = 1 2.",
    "(3.4)For even w, the ground state is degenerate and is comprised of two states that transform as an su(2) doublet.",
    "They are [|Φ ± w ⟩] σ w, where|Φ + w ⟩ = χ - -w 2 +1 ψ - -w 2 +1 • • • χ - -1 ψ - -1 χ - 0 ψ - 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩, |Φ - w ⟩ = χ - -w 2 ψ - -w 2 • • • χ - -1 ψ - -1 χ - 0 ψ - 0 |m 1, m 2 ⟩,(3.5)andm 1 + m 2 = - w 4, m 1 -m 2 = 1 2."
  ]
}